title: Ambient conversation misreports later-turn listen failures as conversation_idle
updated_at: "2026-07-15T22:50:26Z"
---
## Evidence
In ambient._conversation_after_wake, the listen exception path computes whether the error is a no-speech timeout. The first turn distinguishes no_open from listen_failed, but every exception after a successful turn unconditionally emits ambient.conversation_end with reason conversation_idle. A reproduction with one successful turn followed by RuntimeError("provider unavailable") emitted conversation_idle. Existing tests cover a later no-speech TimeoutError, not provider, mic, or internal failures.

## Expected
Only a genuine later-turn no-speech timeout ends the post-wake conversation as conversation_idle. Other failures retain their error class and are surfaced as failures to logs and HEP consumers.

## Actual
Provider, microphone, and internal listen failures after turn one are indistinguishable from normal operator inactivity.

## Acceptance criteria
- Classify later-turn listen exceptions before choosing the conversation outcome.
- Preserve conversation_idle for genuine no-speech expiration.
- Emit a stable failure reason and useful bounded error detail for provider, mic, and unexpected failures.
- Preserve the last successful turn metadata without presenting the failure as normal idle.
- Add tests for later no-speech timeout, ProviderError, mic-busy failure, and unexpected RuntimeError.
- Keep first-turn no_open and listen_failed behavior compatible.